> PROFESSOR:        KONSTANTIN DEGTYAREV

> Campus:                Moscow
> Target Faculties:      Computer Science
> Target Programs:       Artificial Intelligence, Data Analysis
> Available for:         Bachelor's 4th, Master's 2nd
> Proposal Project Type: Course Work (Курсовая работа)
> Format:                Research
> Language:              English

> Detailed Description:
This project, under the guidance of Professor Konstantin Degtyarev, is a research-oriented exploration that delves into the intersection of biology and the Internet of Things (IoT). This study seeks to leverage cutting-edge IoT technology to enhance and innovate within the field of biology. Students from the faculties of Computer Science, specializing in Artificial Intelligence and Data Analysis, are eligible for participation in this project. By combining their skills and knowledge, participants will work on integrating IoT solutions into biological research and experimentation, potentially revolutionizing data collection, monitoring, and analysis in the field of biology.
> Application Requirements:
- Open to Bachelor's 4th-year and Master's 2nd-year students in Computer Science.
- Strong interest in the application of IoT technology in the context of biology.
- Prior experience or coursework related to IoT or biology is advantageous but not mandatory.
> Expected Results:
- Innovative IoT solutions applied to biological research and analysis.
- Enhanced data collection and monitoring capabilities.
- Research findings and insights on the practical applications of IoT in biology.
- Comprehensive research report summarizing the project's objectives and outcomes.

