> DECISION:         APPROVED (APPLIED)
> Project Name:     Significance of Documentation in Software Development
> Название проекта: Значение документации при разработке программного обеспечения
> PROFESSOR:        KONSTANTIN DEGTYAREV

> Campus:                Moscow
> Target Faculties:      Computer Science
> Target Programs:       System and Software Engineering, Aritifical Intelligence
> Available for:         Master's 1st, Master's 2nd
> Proposal Project Type: Course Work (Курсовая работа)
> Format:                Research
> Language:              English

> Detailed Description:
Through this research, participants will embark on a profound journey to unearth the intricate relationship between effective documentation practices and the triumph of software development endeavors. Our mission is to uncover how meticulous and well-structured documentation, from the embryonic stages of project design to the complexities of post-implementation maintenance, can revolutionize the landscape of software development. We will employ rigorous research methods and in-depth analysis to examine the far-reaching implications of this often-overlooked aspect, stretching from project management and collaborative prowess to streamlined code maintenance and knowledge transfer within development teams.
By the conclusion of this endeavor, our objective is to provide the software development community with a wealth of recommendations and insights that will undoubtedly elevate the practice of documentation to an indispensable art form within our discipline. These findings will have a lasting impact not only on the programs of System and Software Engineering and Artificial Intelligence but also on the broader software development landscape.
> Application Requirements:
- This project is available for Master's 1st and Master's 2nd-year students in the fields of System and Software Engineering and Artificial Intelligence.
- Prospective participants should demonstrate a strong interest in software development processes, project management, and the importance of documentation in these contexts.
- Prior coursework or experience in software engineering and documentation practices is advantageous but not mandatory.
> Expected Results:
- In-depth research findings showcasing the significance of documentation in software development.
- Comprehensive analysis of the impact of documentation on project management, collaboration, and code maintenance.
- Recommendations for best practices in documentation, tailored to System and Software Engineering and Artificial Intelligence programs.
- The creation of a detailed research report summarizing the objectives, methods, and outcomes of the project.

> Attachments: Attahment 12, Attachment 13

